{
  "texts": [
    "The only difference was that in Experiment 2 the stimuli were selected using the Distributed method instead of the Random one, and the number of Critical Lures and Unrelated Lures were both set to 3.",
    "The procedure was identical to Experiment 1.",
    "Data analysis was identical to Experiment 1.",
    "Trials with reaction times faster than 300 ms or slower than 3000 ms were excluded from the analysis (1.1% of the trials excluded).",
    "The first GLMM (marginal Pseudo-R 2 =.21; total Pseudo-R 2 =.39) showed that the effect of type of item was significant, χ 2 = 211, p <.001 (Fig. 6A)."
  ]
}